ARGUMENT

| Step | Hyp | Ref | Expression |
|---|---|---|---|

| 1 |  | ralxfr.1 | |- ( y e. C -> A e. B ) |
| 2 |  | ralxfr.2 | |- ( x e. B -> E. y e. C x = A ) |
| 3 |  | ralxfr.3 | |- ( x = A -> ( ph <-> ps ) ) |
| 4 | 3 | #P_rspcv | |- ( A e. B -> ( A. x e. B ph -> ps ) ) |

| 6 | 5 | #P_com12 | |- ( A. x e. B ph -> ( y e. C -> ps ) ) |

| 8 |  | #P_nfra1 | |- F/ y A. y e. C ps |
| 9 |  | #P_nfv | |- F/ y ph |
| 10 |  | #P_rsp | |- ( A. y e. C ps -> ( y e. C -> ps ) ) |
| 11 | 3 | #P_biimprcd | |- ( ps -> ( x = A -> ph ) ) |
| 12 | 10, 11 | #P_syl6 | |- ( A. y e. C ps -> ( y e. C -> ( x = A -> ph ) ) ) |
| 13 | 8, 9, 12 | #P_rexlimd | |- ( A. y e. C ps -> ( E. y e. C x = A -> ph ) ) |
| 14 | 2, 13 | #P_syl5 | |- ( A. y e. C ps -> ( x e. B -> ph ) ) |
| 15 | 14 | #P_ralrimiv | |- ( A. y e. C ps -> A. x e. B ph ) |
| 16 | 7, 15 | #P_impbii | |- ( A. x e. B ph <-> A. y e. C ps ) |

 Transfer universal quantification from a variable ` x ` to another variable ` y ` contained in expression ` A ` .  This proof does not use ~ ralxfrd .  (Contributed by NM, 10-Jun-2005.)  (Revised by Mario Carneiro, 15-Aug-2014.)  (Proof modification is discouraged.) (New usage is discouraged.)
